    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** (74.75) and **Junior Caminero** (72.66) as our primary offensive engines. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a steady matchup against Warren, while **Junior Caminero** draws significant value from an 11% boost against Bradley\u2019s xERA of 4.45, providing high-ceiling production despite a slight park penalty. **Trea Turner** (67.15) remains a mandatory start due to his leadoff positioning and the scarcity value of his speed, paired with a favorable outlook against Holmes. **Caleb Durbin** also demands attention today; despite hitting lower in the order, his massive 32% combined boost from park factors and SP skill makes him an elite utilization option (69.42) against Young. \n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved **Carson Benge** (48.62), who narrowly missed the cut. While **Carson Benge** projects as a serviceable bat, he lacks the aggressive situational boosts currently enjoyed by **Luke Raley** (57.02) and **Hyeseong Kim** (57.80), whose respective platoon edges and SP matchups provide a higher efficiency floor for our 5x5 needs. We are monitoring **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (50.93) closely; his score is contingent on confirmed lineup placement. If **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is bumped from the #9 spot or faces a pinch-hit risk, he becomes a prime candidate to be subbed out to preserve game caps, as his current score is heavily tethered to his aggressive platoon advantage against Sheehan. With **Christian Yelich**, **Colt Keith**, and **Victor Scott II** all currently unavailable, the integrity of our depth relies on these high-efficiency pivots.",
